About Prospect Insights

This section serves two purposes. The first purpose is to provide additional information about the interests of your prospective audience. The second purpose is to act as quality control. Seeing similar key words and “bi-grams” (two words commonly seen in the same bio) assure the supplied pool of prospects is a close fit with your existing audience.

About EOI

Engagement Optimization Insights (EOI) uses a powerful yet understandable algorithm to create actionable insights aimed at improving user engagement. There are many variables contributing to the engagement level of a tweet, including the message of the content itself. You control the message, but our algorithm can make suggestions on how to structure that message to optimize engagement measured by favorites and retweets. Current factors we consider for predicting engagement are time, average words (counted), length of average word, and total length of message. Immediately below, we see your top performing tweets (measured by favorites). Further below we see an analysis of factors effecting performance.

About Factor Analysis

Here we can see the predictive value of the different variables and how they effect favorites. There are some linear effects, such as increasing http links correlating with LOWER engagement (measured by favorites) or a increase in the use of numbers (eg. 5 ways to calm down in 1 minute) correlating with HIGHER engagement. There are also mixed effects such as time of tweet (UTC Timezone) or Capital letters used per tweet.
